## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/) and Docker Compose
- A free [Groq API key](https://console.groq.com/)

### 1. Clone the repo

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/AuraDoc.git
cd AuraDoc
```

### 2. Set up your environment variables

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Open `.env` and add your Groq API key:

```
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here
```

### 3. Run with Docker

```bash
docker-compose up --build
```

Then open [http://localhost:8501](http://localhost:8501) in your browser.

---

## Running Locally (without Docker)

Make sure you have Python 3.10+ and a running MongoDB instance.

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
streamlit run app.py
```

> MongoDB is expected at `mongodb://mongodb:27017/` by default (matches the Docker service name). If running locally, update the connection string in `app.py` to `mongodb://localhost:27017/`.

